---
title: Spicy Thai-Style Vegan Grain Salad with Tomato, Cucumber, Scallions & Peanuts
description: Bold Thai-inspired flavors take this grain and veggie salad to the next level! A sweet and spicy dressing brightens up up a mix of fresh greens, cucumber, tomato, and our hearty grain blend. Top with toasted peanuts, fried onions, and crispy wonton strips for a colorful meal that hits the table in a speedy 20 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6765a5319bfc6de73c8e1d52-761e7f4e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6765a5319bfc6de73c8e1d52-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-thai-style-vegan-grain-salad-6765a5319bfc6de73c8e1d52
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 12 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 770 mg
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Massage @Microwavable Grain Blend{1%unit} in package to separate grains; partially open
package. Microwave until warmed through, ~{1 1/2-2%minutes}.

Spread grain blend out on a #plate{} to cool slightly.

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @Lime{1%unit}. Trim and halve @Mini Cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Quarter @Tomato{1%unit} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄4-inch-thick quarter-moons. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}.

Crush @Peanuts{1%ounce} in their #bag{} (use a #rolling pin{} or a heavy #pan{}).

Heat a #small dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add peanuts and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to plate with grain blend.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much @Sriracha{1%tsp} as you like.

> For 4 servings, use 4 TBSP olive oil and a big squeeze of lime juice.

To bowl with dressing, add @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, cucumber, tomato, scallions, grains and peanuts, half the @Crispy Fried Onions{1%unit}, half the @Wonton Strips{1%unit}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Taste and season with more salt and pepper and a squeeze of lime juice if desired.

Divide grain salad between shallow #bowls{}; top with remaining crispy onions and remaining wonton strips. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.